This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses Support Vector Machines (SVMs) which are a well-established Machine Learning algorithm. Additionally, the paper presents a new approach for the automatic design of kernels using Genetic Programming, which is a popular technique in the Machine Learning community. 

The paper also touches on Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as Genetic Programming is a subfield of AI. 

Neural Networks (cs.NE) could also be a possible sub-category as SVMs are often compared to neural networks in terms of their performance and capabilities. 

Data Mining (cs.DM) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of SVMs on standard Machine Learning benchmarks. 

Finally, the paper's focus on co-evolution could also place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category as co-evolution is often used in the design of control systems.
